(listed as
Dacus cucurbitae
) was recovered from papaya (
C. papaya
) which originated in Hawaii and was intercepted at a port in California (1 interception in nonentry host) between 1 July 1945 and 30 June 1946 (number of individuals recovered and life stages not reported). Taxonomic identification was done by entomologists of the Bureau of Entomology and Plant Quarantine, USDA. Lab Infestation:

